A 17-year-old youth was feared dead today after he plunged into the River Clyde in Glasgow city centre. Divers search River Clyde for missing Gorbals teenager A 17-year-old youth was feared dead today after he plunged into the River Clyde in Glasgow city centre.Police divers hunting for Steven Clark were focusing their search on a stretch of the river near the Broomielaw.The teenager, from Gorbals, was out with a group of friends when the incident happened.The alarm was raised about 7.20pm last night by friends and a full-scale search was launched.A police spokesman said: &quot;Mr Clark was last seen entering the river near the suspensionfootbridge from Carlton Place.&quot;The search to find him has re-commenced using specialist officers from the Police Scotland Dive and Marine Unit.&quot; 